figure.head:
Detail of the stele dated 483. Unearthed in Maoxian, Sichuan;
                                    Sichuan Museum 四川博物院, Chengdu.
                                    Photograph taken in 2016

div.p:
The colophon by Nun (
                                    bhikṣuṇī
                                ) Famen 法門 and others is placed next to JS 10, the Buddha
                                King of Great Emptiness inscription, in our reconstruction (fig.
                                    ).
                                Others have suggested alternative positions.
